cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a randomized algorithm for training Support Vector Machines (SVMs) on large datasets. It also discusses the use of random projections and iterative algorithms for SVM training, which are common techniques in machine learning. 

It could also belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it discusses the combinatorial dimension of SVMs and proposes an iterative algorithm for training SVMs on subsets of data. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another likely category as SVMs are a popular machine learning technique used in AI applications. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision) is a possible category as SVMs are commonly used in image classification and object recognition tasks, which are common in computer vision. 

Finally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as SVMs are sometimes used as an alternative to neural networks for classification and regression tasks.
